## How to Run

### Step 1: Set Google OAuth2 Credentials

Edit `d:\InternShip_Recommender\backend\src\main\resources\application.yml`:
```yaml
spring:
  security:
    oauth2:
      client:
        registration:
          google:
            client-id: YOUR_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID      # ← paste here
            client-secret: YOUR_GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET  # ← paste here
```

> Get credentials at [console.cloud.google.com](https://console.cloud.google.com)
> → APIs & Services → Credentials → Create OAuth2 Client ID (Web app)
> → Redirect URI: `http://localhost:8080/login/oauth2/code/google`

### Step 2: Start the Spring Boot Backend

```powershell
cd d:\InternShip_Recommender\backend
mvn spring-boot:run
```
Runs on **http://localhost:8080**

### Step 3: Start the React Frontend

```powershell
cd d:\InternShip_Recommender\Sample
npm run dev
```
Runs on **http://localhost:5173**

